  "doc_id": "47610",
  "text": "We hypothesize that the transition between particle delivery mechanisms plays a role in benthos population density [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , and that the high-population densities of filter-feeding benthos along basin margins correspond with the deepest depth at which particle delivery to the bottom is enhanced year-round by both onshore advection and vertical turbulent mixing. Excessive turbulence may drive populations to deeper, calmer depths [CITATION_3] ), but where food and habitat are the only limiting factors, the advantage lies in close proximity to where the quantity and quality of POM flux is initially enhanced by vertical convection [CITATION_4] ).",
